{"actual_usd":0.156665,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":226,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30655,"reply":"\"No—if he were only an example, the Cross is a terrible waste.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, the morning light catching on my white tie while the square goes quiet around us for a beat.* \"A teacher can live beautifully and say, ‘Do this.’ But Jesus speaks as the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world. An example can show me the road; he cannot carry my guilt, break death’s claim, or reconcile me to God.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of my Bible.* \"If all I needed was instruction, then yes—live well, preach clearly, die old. But the Christian claim is harsher and kinder than that: I do not just need coaching. I need saving. ‘Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures’—that’s the center of it. The Cross isn’t the tragic ending to a good man’s life. It’s the place where mercy tells the truth about sin without leaving us under it.\"\n\n\"What’s pressing on this for you—the logic of it, or whether it feels just?\"","rolling_24h_usd":48.471595000000036,"run_id":"24bffac2-a782-405a-bed1-5f0853fc3e64"}
